03718nam a22004695i 9780773588363DE-B159720230529101353.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230529t20132013xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97807735883637 a10.1515/97807735883632doi  a(DE-B1597)655068  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 4aBX4629.C68 ǂb H39 2013eb 7aREL0100002bisacsh04a944/.211 aHayden, J. Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut14aThe Catholicisms of Coutances :bVarieties of Religion in Early Modern France, 1350-1789 /cJ. Michael Hayden. 1aMontreal ;aKingston ;aLondon ;aChicago : bMcGill-Queen's University Press, c[2013] 4c©2013  a1 online resource (384 p.) :b4 maps  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda0 aMcGill-Queen's Studies in the History of Religion ;v26400tFront Matter -- tContents -- tMaps and Graph -- tAbbreviations -- tPreface -- tIntroduction -- tCoutances, Its People and History -- tOfficial and Unofficial Catholicism in Early Modern Coutances -- tThe Catholicisms of the Bishops of Coutances -- tThe Catholicisms of the Clerical Elite of Coutances -- tThe Catholicisms of the Religious of Coutances -- tThe Catholicisms of the Parish Clergy of Coutances -- tThe Catholicisms of the Catholic Laity of Coutances -- tThe Other Catholicisms of Coutances -- tConclusion: The Catholicisms of Coutances in Their Norman Context -- tAppendices -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aThe Catholicisms of Coutances is a richly detailed account of France from the Hundred Years' War to the French revolution. Coining the word "catholicisms" to denote the complex varieties of religious beliefs and practices within the Church, J. Michael Hayden presents a detailed analysis of the diocese of Coutances - chosen because of the unusually large number of records available - to shed light on the many ways in which religion developed and affected life in early modern France. Opening with a geographical and chronological sketch of the diocese, Hayden describes the catholicisms of mid-fourteenth century Coutances, discussing their evolution and effects over four hundred years. Employing a wide array of primary sources, the book provides a meticulous study that includes qualitative analyses of papal and diocesan documents and synodal statutes, a quantitative analysis of ordination and pastoral visit records, and a combination of both forms of analysis of the cahiers prepared for the Estates General of 1789. The Catholicisms of Coutances is an innovative contribution to contemporary understandings of Catholic beliefs and practices in the early modern period and their profound effect on the people of a diocese.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aHistoryzFrance. 7aRELIGION / Christianity / Catholic.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077358836340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773588363423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773588363/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles